#. @info:tooltip Help text for hexadecimal code.
#: colordialog.cpp:191
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid ""
"<p>Hexadecimal color code, as used in HTML: #RRGGBB</p><p>RR: two-digit code "
"for red: 00тБатАУтБаFF</p><p>GG: two-digit code for green: 00тБатАУтБаFF</p><p>BB: two-digit "
"code for blue: 00тБатАУтБаFF</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p>Hexadecim├бln├н k├│d barvy, jak se pou┼╛├нv├б v HTML: #RRGGBB</p><p>RR: "
"dvoucifern├╜ k├│d pro ─Нervenou: 00тБатАУтБаFF</p><p>GG: dvoucifern├╜ k├│d pro zelenou: "
"00тБатАУтБаFF</p><p>BB: dvoucifern├╜ k├│d pro modrou: 00тБатАУтБаFF</p>"

#. @info:tooltip Help text for HSL (hue, saturation, lightness). Saturation: 0 means something on the grey axis; 255 means something between the grey axis and the most colorful color. This is different from тАЬchromaтАЭ and should therefore get a different translation. Lightness: 0 means always black; 255 means always white. This is different from тАЬbrightnessтАЭ and should therefore get a different translation.
#: colordialog.cpp:204
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid ""
"<p>Hue: 0┬░тБатАУтБа360┬░</p><p>HSL-Saturation: 0%тБатАУтБа100%</p><p>Lightness: 0%тБатАУтБа100%</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p>Odst├нn: 0┬░тБатАУтБа360┬░</p><p>HSL тАУ sytost: 0 %тБатАУтБа100 %</p><p>Jas: 0 %тБатАУтБа100 %</p>"

#. @info:tooltip Help text for HWB (hue, whiteness, blackness). The idea behind is that the hue defines the pure (maximum colorful) color. Than, white color can be added, creating a тАЬtintтАЭ. Or black color can be added, creating a тАЬshadeтАЭ. Or both can be added, creating a тАЬtoneтАЬ. See https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tint,_shade_and_tone for more information. 0% white + 0% black = pure color. 100% white + 0% black = white. 0% white + 100% black = black. 50% white + 50% black = gray. 50% white + 0% black = tint. 25% white + 25% black = tone. 0% white + 50% black = shade.
#: colordialog.cpp:218
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid "<p>Hue: 0┬░тБатАУтБа360┬░</p><p>Whiteness: 0%тБатАУтБа100%</p><p>Blackness: 0%тБатАУтБа100%</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p>Odst├нn: 0┬░тБатАУтБа360┬░</p><p>B─Ыlost: 0 %тБатАУтБа100 %</p><p>─Мernost: 0 %тБатАУтБа100 %</p>"

#. @info:tooltip Help text for HSV/HSB. HSV (hue, saturation, value) and HSB (hue, saturation, brightness) are two different names for the very same color model. Saturation: 0 means something between black and white; 255 means something between black and the most colorful color. This is different from тАЬchromaтАЭ and should therefore get a different translation. Brightness/value: 0 means always black; 255 means something between white and the most colorful color. This is different from тАЬlightnessтАЭ and should therefore get a different translation.
#: colordialog.cpp:231
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid ""
"<p>Hue: 0┬░тБатАУтБа360┬░</p><p>HSV/HSB-Saturation: 0%тБатАУтБа100%</p><p>Brightness/Value: "
"0%тБатАУтБа100%</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p>Odst├нn: 0┬░тБатАУтБа360┬░</p><p>HSV/HSB тАУ sytost: 0 %тБатАУтБа100 %</p><p>Jas/Hodnota: 0 "
"%тБатАУтБа100 %</p>"

